HEADWORD: information theory
<hw>in`for*ma"tion the"o*ry</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<fld>(Math., Telecommunications)</fld> <def>The science which studies
the capacity of systems to contain, store, and transmit
<er>information</er>{2 and 4}, and the factors such as noise and channel
capacity that may affect the rate or accuracy of information
transmission and reception.</def>⟦br⟧
